cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.PF, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the performance analysis and optimization of a wireless network, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves the analysis of the throughput performance of CSMA networks, which can be related to information theory.
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with the optimization of network throughput, which is a key aspect of social and information networks.
4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper focuses on the performance analysis and optimization of CSMA networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves the analysis of the throughput performance of a wireless network, which can be related to multimedia applications that require high network throughput.
